17 election ballot shall file a notice of candidacy, giving his or her name, residence address,
18 and the office sought, in the office of the Secretary of State no earlier than 9:00 A.M. on
19 the Monday of the eleventh week immediately prior to the election and no later
20 than 12:00 Noon on the Friday immediately following such Monday, notwithstanding the
21 fact that any such days may be legal holidays;
22 (2) Each candidate for solicitor-general of a state court, a county judicial office, a local
23 board of education office, or an office of a consolidated government, or the candidate's
24 agent, desiring to have his or her name placed on the nonpartisan election ballot shall file
25 notice of candidacy in the office of the superintendent no earlier than 9:00 A.M. on the
26 Monday of the eleventh week immediately prior to the election and no later than 12:00
27 Noon on the Friday immediately following such Monday, notwithstanding the fact that
28 any such days may be legal holidays;"
29 SECTION 2.
30 Said chapter is further amended by revising subsection (a) of Code Section 21-2-139, relating
31 to nonpartisan elections authorized and conduct, as follows:
32 "(a) Notwithstanding any other provisions of this chapter to the contrary, the General
33 Assembly may provide by local Act for the election in nonpartisan elections of candidates
34 to fill the office of district attorney, the office of solicitor-general of the state court, county
35 judicial offices, offices of local boards of education, and offices of consolidated
36 governments which are filled by the vote of the electors of said such judicial circuit,
37 county, or political subdivision. Except as otherwise provided in this Code section, the
38 procedures to be employed in such nonpartisan elections shall conform as nearly as
39 practicable to the procedures governing nonpartisan elections as provided in this chapter.
40 Except as otherwise provided in this Code section, the election procedures established by
41 any existing local law which provides for the nonpartisan election of candidates to fill
42 county offices shall conform to the general procedures governing nonpartisan elections as
