43 provided in this chapter, and such nonpartisan elections shall be conducted in accordance
44 with the applicable provisions of this chapter, notwithstanding the provisions of any
45 existing local law. For those offices for which the General Assembly, pursuant to this
46 Code section, provided by local Act for election in nonpartisan primaries and elections,
47 such offices shall no longer require nonpartisan primaries. Such officers shall be elected
48 in nonpartisan elections held and conducted in conjunction with the general primary in
49 even-numbered years in accordance with this chapter without a prior nonpartisan primary.
50 This Code section shall apply to all nonpartisan elections for members of consolidated
51 governments. All nonpartisan elections for members of consolidated governments shall
52 be governed by the provisions of this Code section and shall be considered county elections
53 and not municipal elections for the purposes of this Code section. Nonpartisan elections
54 for municipal offices shall be conducted on the dates provided in the municipal charter."
55 SECTION 3.
56 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
